none: Den Haag, Huis van het boek: MMW 10 A 12

This is a large and beautifully decorated manuscript, made in 1410-1421 in the region of Paris. It contains the French translation of a number of books of Augustine of Hippo's De Civitate Dei by Raoul de Presle (1316-1382): La Cité de Dieu (Books XI-XXII). The date and localisation are based on the illumination: the manuscript features painted miniatures, border decoration with gold and decorated initials.
Willem H.J. van Westreenen van Tielland

Jesuits of the College of Clermont, Paris. Acquired by Willem H.J. van Westreenen van Tielland (1783-1848) of The Hague from the collection of J. Meerman (d. 1815), although not at the Meerman-auction of 1824. Bequeathed to the State of the Netherlands, under the precondition of the foundation of a museum (founded in 1852).
